####################################################
#                                                  #
#                    README.TXT                    #
#                                                  #
#       Timetabling Application in AnsProlog       #
#        Displayed with the use of Python3         #
#                                                  #
#            Written by Oliver Broomhall           #
#                Created 17/08/2017                #
#                                                  #
####################################################
#                                                  #
# Required files:                                  #
#                                                  #
# [*] timetable.lp                                 #
# [*] constraints.lp                               #
# [*] display.py                                   #
# [*] failedTimetable.lp                           #
# [*] edgeCases.lp                                 #
#                                                  #
####################################################
#                                                  #
# How to run:                                      #
#                                                  #
#  To output a timetable, input the whole of the   #
#   following code onto one line of a terminal:    #
#                                                  #
#  $ clingo <aspfile.lp> constraints.lp -n 1       #
#  --outf=2 | python3 display.py                   #
#                                                  #
#  where <aspfile.lp> is either:                   #
#   timetable.lp                                   #
#   failedTimetable.lp                             #
#   edgeCases.lp                                   #
#                                                  #
####################################################
#                                                  #
# How to interpret the output:                     #
#                                                  #
#  The timetable should be output with column      #
#   headings; Day, Time, Room, Unit, Lecturer and  #
#   Students. An example entry to the table is as  #
#   follows:                                       #
#                                                  #
#  Day: Wednesday                                  #
#  Time: 10:00                                     #
#  Room: 201                                       #
#  Unit: Physics                                   #
#  Lecturer: Mr. Doe                               #
#  Student: John                                   #
#                                                  #
#  All entries are shown at the same time, sorted  #
#   by each successive column.                     #
#                                                  #
####################################################
#                                                  #
#                     ENJOY!                       #
#                                                  #
####################################################